{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a59517334c4237e2", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# AISHELL6-whisper: A Chinese Mandarin Audio-visual Whisper Speech Dataset with Speech Recognition Baselines\narXiv: 2509.23833\nAuthors: Cancan Li, Fei Su, Juan Liu, Hui Bu, Yulong Wan, Hongbin Suo, Ming Li\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present AISHELL6-Whisper, the largest open-source Chinese Mandarin audio-visual whisper speech dataset featuring 30 hours each of parallel whisper and normal speech with synchronized frontal facial videos.\n  2. We propose an audio-visual speech recognition baseline based on the Whisper-Flamingo framework that integrates a parallel training strategy to align embeddings across speech types.\n  3. We introduce a lightweight projection layer specifically designed to adapt the model to whisper speech's spectral properties and bridge the acoustic gap with normal speech.\n  4. Our proposed model achieves a Character Error Rate of 4.13% for whisper speech and 1.11% for normal speech on the AISHELL6-Whisper test set.\n  5. Our approach establishes new state-of-the-art results on the public wTIMIT benchmark, demonstrating strong cross-lingual transferability.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/训练-SSL微调, ASR/训练-监督", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "eb498e74-5546-46cd-a7c5-15e921cd39f4", "uuid": "c722f7bc-4462-43c3-9b27-0fd0f9f413da", "timestamp": "2026-07-13T08:10:50.670Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# AISHELL6-whisper: A Chinese Mandarin Audio-visual Whisper Speech Dataset with Speech Recognition Baselines\narXiv: 2509.23833\nAuthors: Cancan Li, Fei Su, Juan Liu, Hui Bu, Yulong Wan, Hongbin Suo, Ming Li\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: speech_dataset\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present AISHELL6-Whisper, the largest open-source Chinese Mandarin audio-visual whisper speech dataset featuring 30 hours each of parallel whisper and normal speech with synchronized frontal facial videos.\n  2. We propose an audio-visual speech recognition baseline based on the Whisper-Flamingo framework that integrates a parallel training strategy to align embeddings across speech types.\n  3. We introduce a lightweight projection layer specifically designed to adapt the model to whisper speech's spectral properties and bridge the acoustic gap with normal speech.\n  4. Our proposed model achieves a Character Error Rate of 4.13% for whisper speech and 1.11% for normal speech on the AISHELL6-Whisper test set.\n  5. Our approach establishes new state-of-the-art results on the public wTIMIT benchmark, demonstrating strong cross-lingual transferability.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/训练-SSL微调, ASR/训练-监督", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
