><span id=\"A1.T4.3.5.4.6.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">51.20</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.5.4.7\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.5.4.7.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">27.99</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<th id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_th ltx_th_row ltx_border_bb ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\" rowspan=\"2\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">40h_mix</span></th>\n<th id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_th ltx_th_row ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Unseen</span></th>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">59.52</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.4\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.4.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">33.74</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.5\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.5.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">59.19</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.6\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.6.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">33.26</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.7\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.7.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">59.85</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.8\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_t\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.6.5.8.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">34.22</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6\" class=\"ltx_tr\">\n<th id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.1\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_left ltx_th ltx_th_row ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">Seen</span></th>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.2\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.2.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">56.29</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.3\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.3.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">31.22</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.4\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.4.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">60.56</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.5\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.5.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">33.54</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.6\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.6.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">52.15</span></td>\n<td id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.7\" class=\"ltx_td ltx_align_center ltx_border_bb\" style=\"padding-left:4.0pt;padding-right:4.0pt;\"><span id=\"A1.T4.3.7.6.7.1\" class=\"ltx_text\" style=\"font-size:90%;\">28.93</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section id=\"A1.SS3\" class=\"ltx_subsection\">\n<h3 class=\"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection\">\n<span class=\"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection\">A.3 </span>Robustness to Demographic Distribution</h3>\n\n<div id=\"A1.SS3.p1\" class=\"ltx_para\">\n<p id=\"A1.SS3.p1.1\" class=\"ltx_p\">To complement the main experiments, we analyze robustness with respect to demographic variation, focusing on potential performance differences across speaker gender.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"A1.SS3.p2\" class=\"ltx_para ltx_noindent\">\n<p id=\"A1.SS3.p2.1\" class=\"ltx_p\"><span id=\"A1.SS3.p2.1.1\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_bold\">Setup.</span>\nTo analyze robustness with respect to demographic variation, we evaluate models trained on three different subsets of the data: (i) male-only speakers (40h_males), (ii) female-only speakers (40h_females), and (iii) a mixed subset (40h_mix). Each model is evaluated on both <span id=\"A1.SS3.p2.1.2\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_italic\">seen</span> and <span id=\"A1.SS3.p2.1.3\" class=\"ltx_text ltx_font_italic\">unseen</span> speakers. In addition to global WER and CER, we report performance separately for male (M) and female (F) speakers in the test set.</p>", "numLines": 300, "startLine": 1100, "totalLines": 1525}}}
